Proposal
The Scheme for Financing Scheduled Caste Cooperative Societies has been operationalized in the year 2004-2005.

On the proposals pending since 2012 for financing Scheduled Caste Industrial Cooperative Societies, Shri. As per the Government decision dated 24th October, 2018, a State Level Committee under the Chairmanship of Joint Secretary (AJAC) has been constituted to scrutinize about 449 proposals pending with the Commissioner, Social Welfare, Pune. Accordingly, out of these 449 pending proposals received from the Government, Aviation Backward Class Industrial

Limitation of Producer Co-operative Societies. , Thackeray Nagar, CIDCO T.G. Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is the PATA of the organization. It was under the consideration of the Government to grant financial assistance to the Institute subject to the fulfilment of the conditions and conditions of the Government decision as may be prescribed by the Government from time to time.
The government's decision:

G. Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar. Job Work and Spare Part Manufacturing Forging Job Work Production Plant for a total cost of Rs. A project worth ₹1 lakh is proposed in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar district. Under the Scheme of Financing Scheduled Caste Co-operative Societies to the present institution for the construction of the project, the first instalment out of the provision available in this financial year 2023-24 will be Rs. 50.00 Lakhs (Rupees Fifty Lakhs only) and Long Term Loan of Rs. The sanction of total financial assistance of Rs.100 lakh (Rupees One Hundred Lakh only) amounting to Rs.100 lakh (Rupees Fifty Lakh only) is being accorded in-principle approval subject to the conditions and conditions prescribed under the Scheme.

2. The proposal for the said institution was made by the Commissioner, Social Welfare, Pune, vide Reference No. 11 is submitted to the Government under the letter mentioned herein. The Commissioner, Social Welfare, Pune shall ensure that the Institute has strictly complied with the conditions and conditions prescribed by the Government under the Scheme for Financing Scheduled Castes Industrial Cooperative Societies for sanctioning the first instalment to the Institute.
2. Mother of the institution. It should be ensured that the petition is not filed in the court.

4. Field level officers will conduct physical site inspection of the project before disbursement of funds to these institutions. The funds should be disbursed to these institutions only after the submission of the site report.

The process of determining the interest rate on government loans provided under the scheme is underway at the government level. The interest rate determined by the government will be the interest rate applicable to the loan.

6. Repayment of government loans to these institutions should be initiated after two years from the payment of 70 of the project value due to the institution. The repayment period of the loan will be 6 years. The loan (principal) should be paid in 16 equal quarterly instalments within 4 years and then interest should be collected in 8 equal quarterly instalments over two years.
The amount of equity sanctioned under the scheme is required to be returned by the institution to the government in 10 equal installments within 10 years from the date of completion of the project.

8. The Controlling Officer shall spend the funds indicated in the aforesaid statement. Once the funds are spent, the statement and utilization certificate should be submitted to the government without fail.
9. The Commissioner (Social Welfare) shall, after drawing up the aforesaid funds, subordinate them.
The funds should be disbursed only after the prescribed conditions and defects are met.

10. Commissioner Social Welfare, Maharashtra State, Pune is being declared as the Drawing and Disbursing Officer for the purpose. They are also being empowered to sign copies of the payment to them or to the officer authorised by them.
11. D of this Department. The Commissioner, Social Welfare, Pune shall act in accordance with the provisions of the Government Decision of 6.11.2017.
